quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,85,"And blessed is He to whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them and with whom is knowledge of the Hour and to whom you will be returned."
  43,86,"And those they invoke{1} besides Him do not possess [power of] intercession; but only those who testify to the truth [can benefit], and they know.{2}",footnotes:1:i.e., worship.That intercession is granted exclusively by permission of Allāh to those He wills.
  43,87,"And if you asked them{1} who created them, they would surely say, ",footnotes:1:Those who associate others with Allāh.
  50,10,"And lofty palm trees having fruit arranged in layers -"
  50,11,"As provision for the servants, and We have given life thereby to a dead land. Thus is the emergence [i.e., resurrection]."
  50,12,"The people of Noah denied before them,{1} and the companions of the well{2} and Thamūd",footnotes:1:i.e., before the disbelievers of Makkah.See footnote to 25:38.
  51,4,"And the [angels] apportioning [each] matter,"
  51,5,"Indeed, what you are promised is true."
  51,6,"And indeed, the recompense is to occur."